<subSubSection id="E2FF65012B46FFC4FF5888BEFC0461E6" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph id="AA5A368A2B46FFC4FF5888BEFC7F620B" blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FF5888BEFE8663A6" bold="true" box="[199,345,151,176]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Description.</emphasis>
Erect, massive, stipitate sponge, 70 × 70 × 
<quantity id="6D1D9B6F2B46FFC4FCD188B1FC4163B9" box="[846,926,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
diameter (
<figureCitation id="32DE2A0F2B46FFC4FB8688BEFB5C63A6" box="[1049,1155,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="48.[151,250,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,301,1963]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[150,1436,301,1963]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 20. Phakellia rubra sp. nov. A. In situ; B. Skeletal architecture (B, x5); C. Strongyles (sinuous); D. Style; E. Oxeas; F. Oxeas with hastate modifications" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2651490/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 20A</figureCitation>
). Surface smooth, fleshy and conulose, with a skin-like dermal membrane stretched between the ends of the fibres (lost in preservative). Oscules, 
<quantity id="6D1D9B6F2B46FFC4FF6088F6FE8163E1" box="[255,350,223,248]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
diameter, sunken on the surface. Ostia, &lt;
<quantity id="6D1D9B6F2B46FFC4FCDE88C9FC5B63E1" box="[833,900,224,248]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
diameter spread all over surface. Texture firm, flexible, compressible. Colour in life dark-red; in preservative, beige.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA5A368A2B46FFC4FF58890EFB9562E3" blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FF58890EFEF16256" bold="true" box="[199,302,295,320]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Skeleton</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="32DE2A0F2B46FFC4FEA0890EFE796256" box="[319,422,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="48.[151,250,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,301,1963]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[150,1436,301,1963]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 20. Phakellia rubra sp. nov. A. In situ; B. Skeletal architecture (B, x5); C. Strongyles (sinuous); D. Style; E. Oxeas; F. Oxeas with hastate modifications" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2651490/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 20B</figureCitation>
). Choanosomal skeleton consists of a dense interwoven mass of sinuous strongyles and styles. Axial spicules disposed longitudinally in a dendritic fashion. Spicule tracts definable for very short distance in choanosome before becoming obscured. Choanosomal peripheral region not well formed; spicules predominantly styles and oxeas, arranged individually, branching tangentially from the axis becoming plumoreticulate and protrude through the ectosome. Styles in the axial and peripheral skeleton do not appear to be differentiated, overlying the axial strongyles. Specialized ectosomal skeleton absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA5A368A2B46FFC4FF5889D6FD856193" blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FF5889D6FE14610E" bold="true" box="[199,459,511,536]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Spicules. Megascleres</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="32DE2A0F2B46FFC4FE4389D6FDF0610E" box="[476,559,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="48.[151,250,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,301,1963]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[150,1436,301,1963]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 20. Phakellia rubra sp. nov. A. In situ; B. Skeletal architecture (B, x5); C. Strongyles (sinuous); D. Style; E. Oxeas; F. Oxeas with hastate modifications" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2651490/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
C–F). Strongyles, sinuous, occasional stylote modifications occur, 901 (895– 911) × 3 (3) µm, n = 10. Styles, usually slightly curved one-third the distance from the head; some distinctly curved midway, 527 (521–532) × 7 (7) µm, n = 10. Oxeas, slightly curved midway, with one end hastate, 389 (384–392) × 6 (6) µm, n = 10. 
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FEC28A45FE2B6193" bold="true" box="[349,500,620,645]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Microscleres</emphasis>
. Absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA5A368A2B46FFC4FF588AA6FEB661DA" blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FF588AA6FD5161BE" bold="true" box="[199,654,655,680]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Substratum, depth range and ecology.</emphasis>
Found usually on coral rubble, in sheltered locations and rock ledges at a depth of 
<specimenCount id="BCE3FD032B46FFC4FEB68A9DFEB661DA" box="[297,361,692,716]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="generic">
<quantity id="6D1D9B6F2B46FFC4FEB68A9DFEBA61DA" box="[297,357,692,716]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="m" value="20.0">20 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA5A368A2B46FFC4FF588AFEFC0461E6" blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" box="[199,987,727,752]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FF588AFEFDDB61E6" bold="true" box="[199,516,727,752]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Geographical distribution.</emphasis>
Sodwana Bay, east coast of 
<collectingCountry id="D2F2761A2B46FFC4FCDB8AFEFC0861E6" box="[836,983,727,752]" name="South Africa" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">South Africa</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E2FF65012B46FFC4FF588AD5FB496002" box="[199,1174,764,789]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AA5A368A2B46FFC4FF588AD5FB496002" blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" box="[199,1174,764,789]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FF588AD5FE916003" bold="true" box="[199,334,764,789]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named for the dark red colour of the sponge (
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FCC98AD5FC4A6003" box="[854,917,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">ruber</emphasis>
meaning dark red, L.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E2FF65012B46FFC4FF588B36FED666D6" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="AA5A368A2B46FFC4FF588B36FED666D6" blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FF588B36FEE4602E" bold="true" box="[199,315,799,824]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="6DE54D092B46FFC4FEDD8B36FE71602E" authorityName="Bowerbank" authorityYear="1862" box="[322,430,799,824]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FEDD8B36FE71602E" box="[322,430,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to, and often confused with, 
<taxonomicName id="6DE54D092B46FFC4FCFA8B36FC01602E" box="[869,990,799,824]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dictyonellidae" genus="Acanthella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FCFA8B36FC01602E" box="[869,990,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Acanthella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the presence of sinuous spicules in the choanosome. They differ primarily in the arrangement of the choanosomal skeleton (
<bibRefCitation id="CE744B7B2B46FFC4FB328B6DFA4F604A" author="Alvarez" box="[1197,1424,836,861]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Alvarez" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref40798" refString="Alvarez, B., Soest, R. W. M. van &amp; Rutzler, K. (1998) A Revision of Axinellidae (Porifera: Demospongiae) in the Central West Atlantic Region. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 598, 1 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.598" type="journal article" year="1998">
Alvarez 
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FA8F8B6CFA9B604B" box="[1296,1348,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al</emphasis>
. 1998
</bibRefCitation>
). Members of 
<taxonomicName id="6DE54D092B46FFC4FEB18B4EFE466096" authorityName="Bowerbank" authorityYear="1862" box="[302,409,871,896]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FEB18B4EFE466096" box="[302,409,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a well-defined axial region and an extra-axial skeleton and a reticulate peripheral skeleton (
<bibRefCitation id="CE744B7B2B46FFC4FE9A8BA5FE6760B2" author="Bergquist" box="[261,440,908,933]" firstAuthor="Bergquist" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 85" refId="ref41305" refString="Bergquist, P. R. (1970) The Marine Fauna of New Zealand: Porifera, Demospongiae, Part 2 (Axinellida and Halichondrida). New Zealand Department of Scientific and Industrial Research Bulletin, New Zealand Oceanographic Institute Memoir 51, 197, 1 - 85." type="journal article" year="1970">Bergquist 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="CE744B7B2B46FFC4FE5B8BA5FD6D60B2" author="Carvalho" box="[452,690,908,933]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Carvalho" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="109 - 116" refId="ref42335" refString="Carvalho, M. S., Desqueyroux-Faundez, R. &amp; Hajdu, E. (2007) Phakellia sur sp. nov. (Demospongiae, Halichondrida, Axinellidae) from the lower slope off Cape Horn (South America), with a revision of the genus. Marine Biology Research, 3, 109 - 116. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 17451000701276063" type="journal article" year="2007">
Carvalho 
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FDAB8BA4FDB860B3" box="[564,615,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="CE744B7B2B46FFC4FD208BA5FC0560B2" author="Alvarez &amp; Hooper" box="[703,986,908,933]" firstAuthor="Alvarez" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="17 - 42" refId="ref40964" refString="Alvarez, B. &amp; Hooper, J. N. A. (2009) Taxonomic revision of the order Halichondrida (Porifera: Demospongiae) from northern Australia. Family Axinellidae. The Beagle, Records of the Museums and Art Galleries of the Northern Territory, 25, 17 - 42." type="journal article" year="2009">Alvarez &amp; Hooper 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Members of 
<taxonomicName id="6DE54D092B46FFC4FB1E8BA5FB2560B3" box="[1153,1274,908,933]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dictyonellidae" genus="Acanthella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FB1E8BA5FB2560B3" box="[1153,1274,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Acanthella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lack the axial and extra-axial skeleton, and have a central axial column producing a dendritic skeleton of branching spicule tracts (
<bibRefCitation id="CE744B7B2B46FFC4FF018BFDFE5160FA" author="Hooper &amp; Levi" box="[158,398,980,1005]" firstAuthor="Hooper" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="191 - 212" refId="ref45284" refString="Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; Levi, C. (1994) Biogeography of Indo-west Pacific sponges: Microcionidae, Raspailiidae, Axinellidae. In: Soest, R. W. M. van, Kempen, T. M. G. van &amp; Braekman, J. C. (Eds.), Sponges in Time and Space. Balkema, Rotterdam, pp. 191 - 212." type="book chapter" year="1994">Hooper &amp; Levi 1994</bibRefCitation>
). This species clearly fits within the definition of 
<taxonomicName id="6DE54D092B46FFC4FC278BFDFBFC60FB" authorityName="Bowerbank" authorityYear="1862" box="[952,1059,980,1005]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FC278BFDFBFC60FB" box="[952,1059,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CE744B7B2B46FFC4FBAD8BFDFAC460FA" author="Carvalho" box="[1074,1307,980,1005]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Carvalho" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="109 - 116" refId="ref42335" refString="Carvalho, M. S., Desqueyroux-Faundez, R. &amp; Hajdu, E. (2007) Phakellia sur sp. nov. (Demospongiae, Halichondrida, Axinellidae) from the lower slope off Cape Horn (South America), with a revision of the genus. Marine Biology Research, 3, 109 - 116. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 17451000701276063" type="journal article" year="2007">
Carvalho 
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FB3E8BFCFB0D60FB" box="[1185,1234,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="CE744B7B2B46FFC4FAB88BFDFEF26706" author="Alvarez &amp; Hooper" firstAuthor="Alvarez" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="17 - 42" refId="ref40964" refString="Alvarez, B. &amp; Hooper, J. N. A. (2009) Taxonomic revision of the order Halichondrida (Porifera: Demospongiae) from northern Australia. Family Axinellidae. The Beagle, Records of the Museums and Art Galleries of the Northern Territory, 25, 17 - 42." type="journal article" year="2009">Alvarez &amp; Hooper 2009</bibRefCitation>
). The majority of 
<taxonomicName id="6DE54D092B46FFC4FE628BDEFDB66706" authorityName="Bowerbank" authorityYear="1862" box="[509,617,1015,1040]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FE628BDEFDB66706" box="[509,617,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are described from all over the world and the genus contains 32 valid of which two are described from the WIO (Van 
<bibRefCitation id="CE744B7B2B46FFC4FD6E8C35FC6D6722" author="Soest" box="[753,946,1052,1077]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Soest" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" refId="ref50982" refString="Soest, R. W. M Van, Boury-Esnault, N., Hooper, J. N. A., Rutzler, K., de Voogd, N. J., Alvarez, B., Hajdu, E., Pisera, A. B., Manconi, R., Schonberg, C., Klautau, M., Picton, B., Kelly, M., Vacelet, J., Dohrmann, M., Diaz, M. C., Cardenas, P., Carballo, J. L., Rios, P. &amp; Downey, R. (2017) World Porifera database. Available from: http: // www. marinespecies. org / porifera (accessed 5 December 2017)" type="url" year="2017">
Soest 
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FCAA8C34FCB16723" box="[821,878,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first record of this genus in the South African region. 
<taxonomicName id="6DE54D092B46FFC4FE098C16FCD4674E" authority="(Dendy, 1916)" authorityName="Dendy" authorityYear="1916" baseAuthorityName="Dendy" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[406,779,1087,1112]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="radiata">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FE098C16FD81674E" box="[406,606,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia radiata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CE744B7B2B46FFC4FDF28C16FCDB674E" author="Dendy" box="[621,772,1087,1112]" firstAuthor="Dendy" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="93 - 146" refId="ref43189" refString="Dendy, A. (1916) Report on the non-Calcareous sponges collected by Mr. James Hornell at Okhamandal in Kattiawar in 1905 - 6. Report to the government of Baroda on the marine zoology of Okhamandal in Kattiawar, 2, 93 - 146, pls. I-IV." type="journal article" year="1916">Dendy, 1916</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, described by 
<bibRefCitation id="CE744B7B2B46FFC4FC2D8C16FB96674E" author="Dendy" box="[946,1097,1087,1112]" firstAuthor="Dendy" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="93 - 146" refId="ref43189" refString="Dendy, A. (1916) Report on the non-Calcareous sponges collected by Mr. James Hornell at Okhamandal in Kattiawar in 1905 - 6. Report to the government of Baroda on the marine zoology of Okhamandal in Kattiawar, 2, 93 - 146, pls. I-IV." type="journal article" year="1916">Dendy (1916</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CE744B7B2B46FFC4FBC98C69FB4D674E" author="Dendy" box="[1110,1170,1088,1112]" firstAuthor="Dendy" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 164" refId="ref43241" refString="Dendy, A. (1922) Report on the Sigmatotetraxonida collected by H. M. S. ' Sealark' in the Indian Ocean. In: Reports of the Percy Sladen Trust Expedition to the Indian Ocean in 1905. Fol. 7. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, Series 2, 18 (1), pp. 1 - 164, pls. 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1922">1922</bibRefCitation>
), is a thin crust (with a large large number of independent but closely located conules on the surface) and differs from the new species in having a dull orange colouration and the presence of trichodragmata. Comparison of spicules dimensions indicates that 
<taxonomicName id="6DE54D092B46FFC4FF578C84FEE867D3" baseAuthorityName="Dendy" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[200,311,1196,1221]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="radiata">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FF578C84FEE867D3" box="[200,311,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. radiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has smaller styles (600 × 
<quantity id="6D1D9B6F2B46FFC4FDC38C85FD7967D2" box="[604,678,1196,1220]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 µm</quantity>
) and strongyles (430 × 
<quantity id="6D1D9B6F2B46FFC4FC2F8C85FC2467D2" box="[944,1019,1196,1220]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="17.0">17 µm</quantity>
) and a skeleton of spicule tracts with a reticulation of rounded meshes. 
<bibRefCitation id="CE744B7B2B46FFC4FDB18CE6FD3667FE" author="Lamarck" box="[558,745,1231,1256]" firstAuthor="Lamarck" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="294 - 312" refId="ref46136" refString="Lamarck, J. B. P. de M. C. de (1814 [1813]) Sur les polypiers empates. Annales du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 1814, 294 - 312 + 370 - 386 + 432 - 458." type="journal article" year="1814">Lamarck (1814)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="6DE54D092B46FFC4FCF18CF8FB6067FE" authority="(Lamarck, 1814)" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1814" baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[878,1215,1231,1256]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="labellum">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FCF18CF8FC2E67FE" box="[878,1009,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. labellum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CE744B7B2B46FFC4FB9A8CE6FB6867FE" author="Lamarck" box="[1029,1207,1231,1256]" firstAuthor="Lamarck" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="294 - 312" refId="ref46136" refString="Lamarck, J. B. P. de M. C. de (1814 [1813]) Sur les polypiers empates. Annales du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 1814, 294 - 312 + 370 - 386 + 432 - 458." type="journal article" year="1814">Lamarck, 1814</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="D2F2761A2B46FFC4FA908CE6FA4667FE" box="[1295,1433,1231,1256]" name="Madagascar" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="6DE54D092B46FFC4FF088CDDFE92661B" authority="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson, 2019" authorityName="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson" authorityYear="2019" box="[151,333,1268,1293]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="rubra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FF088CDDFE92661B" box="[151,333,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FEC88CDDFE6A661B" bold="true" box="[343,437,1268,1293]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="83A257E32B46FFC4FEC88CDDFE6A661B" box="[343,437,1268,1293]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a similar spicule complement to 
<taxonomicName id="6DE54D092B46FFC4FCF18CDCFC30661B" baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[878,1007,1268,1293]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="labellum">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FCF18CDCFC30661B" box="[878,1007,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. labellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in spicule geometry with having two size categories of styles and in that the strongyles are reduced to very thin and sinuous stylesstrongyles. 
<taxonomicName id="6DE54D092B46FFC4FEBF8D15FE236643" baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[288,508,1340,1365]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="labellum">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FEBF8D15FE236643" box="[288,508,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia labellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not since been recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="D2F2761A2B46FFC4FC2D8D15FBE66643" box="[946,1081,1340,1365]" name="Madagascar" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
even though 
<bibRefCitation id="CE744B7B2B46FFC4FB778D15FA436642" author="Thomas, P. A." box="[1256,1436,1340,1365]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="10 - 16" refId="ref51663" refString="Thomas, P. A. (1979 a) Demospongiae of Minicoy Island (Indian Ocean) Part 1 - orders Keratosida and Haplosclerida. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of India, 21 (1 - 2), 10 - 16." type="journal article" year="1979">Thomas (1979)</bibRefCitation>
produced an extensive sponge monograph from this region. Based on the morphological differences between all three species, and the limited distribution potential of sponges, 
<taxonomicName id="6DE54D092B46FFC4FCC38DACFC67668B" authority="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson, 2019" authorityName="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson" authorityYear="2019" box="[860,952,1412,1437]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="rubra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FCC38DACFC67668B" box="[860,952,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FC208DADFBC7668B" bold="true" box="[959,1048,1412,1437]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="83A257E32B46FFC4FC208DADFBC7668B" box="[959,1048,1412,1437]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is considered as a new member of 
<taxonomicName id="6DE54D092B46FFC4FF088D8EFEDD66D6" authorityName="Bowerbank" authorityYear="1862" box="[151,258,1447,1472]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FF088D8EFEDD66D6" box="[151,258,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E2FF65012B46FFC4FF588DE5FD9E651E" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="key">
<paragraph id="AA5A368A2B46FFC4FF588DE5FDDC66F3" blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" box="[199,515,1484,1509]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="9891EA982B46FFC4FF588DE5FDDC66F3" bold="true" box="[199,515,1484,1509]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Key diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA5A368A2B46FFC4FF588DD8FD9E651E" blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" box="[199,577,1519,1544]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">• Sponge massive and stipitate.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E2FF65012B46FFC4FF588E3CFCD06563" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph id="AA5A368A2B46FFC4FF588E3CFE73653B" blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" box="[199,428,1556,1581]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">• Dark red colour.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA5A368A2B46FFC4FF588E10FB926546" blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" box="[199,1101,1591,1616]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">• Axial spicules disposed longitudinally in a dendritic fashion in choanosome.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA5A368A2B46FFC4FF588E74FCD06563" blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" box="[199,783,1628,1653]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">• Strongyles, styles and oxeas present as spicules.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
